---
import RootLayout from "../../layouts/RootLayout.astro";

const lastUpdated = "July 8, 2026";
---

<RootLayout title="Privacy Policy" lang="en">
  <main class="container mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 py-16 leading-relaxed">
    <h1 class="mb-6 text-4xl">Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="mb-8 text-sm uppercase tracking-wide">
      Last updated: {lastUpdated}
    </p>

    <section class="mb-8 space-y-4">
      <h2 class="text-2xl">1. Data Controller</h2>
      <p>
        This policy explains how Harmonia Terra processes personal data through
        the harmoniaworld.org website and the contact channels displayed on the
        website.
      </p>
      <p>
        For questions about personal data, you can contact us at
        <a class="underline" href="mailto:contact@harmoniaworld.org">
          contact@harmoniaworld.org
        </a>.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-8 space-y-4">
      <h2 class="text-2xl">2. Data We May Process</h2>
      <p>We may process data that you voluntarily provide, including:</p>
      <ul class="list-disc space-y-2 pl-6">
        <li>first and last name;</li>
        <li>email address and/or phone number;</li>
        <li>messages and information included in forms or emails;</li>
        <li>information needed for guidance, bookings, or collaborations;</li>
        <li>limited technical data generated when accessing the website.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-8 space-y-4">
      <h2 class="text-2xl">3. Purposes and Legal Bases</h2>
      <p>We process data for the following purposes:</p>
      <ul class="list-disc space-y-2 pl-6">
        <li>responding to guidance, contact, or collaboration requests;</li>
        <li>managing bookings, activities, and communications;</li>
        <li>administering and securing the website;</li>
        <li>complying with applicable legal obligations.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        The legal bases may include your consent, taking steps at your request,
        our legitimate interest in responding to requests and administering the
        website, and applicable legal obligations.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-8 space-y-4">
      <h2 class="text-2xl">4. Google Forms</h2>
      <p>
        The website uses Google Forms for guidance requests and for people
        interested in becoming facilitators. Data entered in these forms is used
        to review and respond to your request.
      </p>
      <p>
        The forms are provided by Google. When you interact with them, Google
        may process data according to its own policies and terms.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-8 space-y-4">
      <h2 class="text-2xl">5. Third-Party Services</h2>
      <p>The website may load or direct users to third-party services:</p>
      <ul class="list-disc space-y-2 pl-6">
        <li>Google Forms, for contact and registration forms;</li>
        <li>Google Maps, for displaying the location;</li>
        <li>Google Calendar API, for displaying public activities;</li>
        <li>WhatsApp and Instagram, for communication and social pages;</li>
        <li>hosting services, which may generate technical access logs.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        These services may process data outside the European Economic Area, in
        accordance with their own policies and transfer mechanisms.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-8 space-y-4">
      <h2 class="text-2xl">6. Cookies</h2>
      <p>
        The website does not use first-party cookies for analytics, advertising,
        or profiling. Embedded third-party services or links, such as Google,
        WhatsApp, or Instagram, may use their own technologies according to
        their policies.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-8 space-y-4">
      <h2 class="text-2xl">7. Data Retention</h2>
      <p>
        We keep data submitted through forms, email, or contact channels until
        the request is resolved, unless the law requires or permits a longer
        retention period.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-8 space-y-4">
      <h2 class="text-2xl">8. Your Rights</h2>
      <p>Under the GDPR, you have the right to request:</p>
      <ul class="list-disc space-y-2 pl-6">
        <li>access to your data;</li>
        <li>rectification of inaccurate data;</li>
        <li>deletion of your data;</li>
        <li>restriction of processing;</li>
        <li>objection to processing;</li>
        <li>data portability, where applicable;</li>
        <li>withdrawal of consent, where processing is based on consent.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        You can contact us at
        <a class="underline" href="mailto:contact@harmoniaworld.org">
          contact@harmoniaworld.org
        </a>
        to exercise these rights. You also have the right to lodge a complaint with
        the relevant data protection authority.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="space-y-4">
      <h2 class="text-2xl">9. Changes</h2>
      <p>
        We may update this policy when we change the website, the services we
        use, or the way we process data.
      </p>
    </section>
  </main>
</RootLayout>
